There are aggressive types of cancer and such types that are inert.
It is therefore necessary to properly explain to the patient the degree of danger of his type of cancer, offer him possible alternatives, not necessarily treat prostate cancer that does not have an impact on life in the long term, and focus in these cases rather on active surveillance of the disease.
Today, many men who have been diagnosed with cancer are not treated because their type of cancer is not aggressive and does not threaten their lives.
