As described by the New York Times, it was the largest event of its kind in the history of the American fast food industry.
But it was attended by only a few hundred people, though not all of them were fast food workers, who employ tens of thousands in New York.
Whether this event will become the spark that ignites the flame of the mass movement is still unclear.
