For example, to control devices in public places, we had a project in which we thought about gestures, but not about sweeping, just about such nimble, short ones.
The gesture would not be taken with the camera of the device, but with a bracelet that would track the movements of bones and muscles.
So far it is large, but theoretically it can be reduced to the size of a wristwatch.
