In my lectures I often say that augmented reality is the seventh consecutive breakthrough in the interaction between man and machine.
I think that the addition of tactile sensations could easily become the eighth breakthrough.
So far, one of the interesting tricks is used - the use of the second hand as a certain kind of basis for imaging.
It records compression in an excellent way!
