Although sulfur burns the throat and stings in the eyes when the wind unexpectedly turns and traps the miners in the dense fumes that come out of the volcano, the miners are so hard that none of them complain that they suffer from serious diseases... but this is evident from their frequent respiratory problems, arthritis, pain.
